    reductions (size-0 ``dim``) the result is ``nan``.
    
    Examples
    --------
    >>> import lucid
    >>> x = lucid.tensor([[1.0, 2.0], [3.0, 4.0]])
    >>> lucid.mean(x)
    Tensor(2.5)
    >>> lucid.mean(x, dim=0)
    Tensor([2., 3.])
